## Quick start

```bash
# 1. Extract the archive
unzip laravel-{{ app_name | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}-inertia-{{ starter_kit }}-docker.zip
cd {{ app_name | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}

# 2. Build and start the containers
docker compose up --build
```

App: `http://localhost:{{ app_port }}`  
Vite dev server: `http://localhost:5173`

> **This archive is fully ready to use.** The project was created with `laravel new`
> on the server — an `APP_KEY` is already set in `.env` and all Docker files are
> pre-configured.

